> Can't get enough of sweet and savory flavor combos? These bowls are just the
> thing. Here, we sear chicken breast strips with a bevy of warming, smoky
> spices, then serve them over scallion-flecked rice with a drizzle of ancho
> lime crema. An easy kiwi and tomato salsa adds sweet, fresh contrast and
> bright color, taking the dish to the next level. One bite will have you
> totally BOWL-ed over.

== Rice ==

Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites
from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion
whites; cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup} to coat, then add @water{1 1/4%cups}. Bring to
a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Kiwi Salsa ==

While rice cooks, finely dice @roma tomato{1}. Peel and finely dice @kiwi{1}.
Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine scallion greens, tomato, kiwi, @sugar{1/4%tsp},
and a big squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season generously with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Ancho Lime Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, lime zest, and
@ancho chili powder{1/4%tsp}. (You'll use more chili powder in the next step.)
Stir in @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add chicken, @southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, and remaining
@ancho chili powder{1%tsp} if desired. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{2%tbsp}, and a big pinch of
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until liquid has reduced and chicken is
coated and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with chicken and salsa. Drizzle with
crema and serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.